{"data":[{"id":"169215845394982","type":"mrk","contents":"SHOW command\n======\nOverview\n------\nYou can conveniently use the \"SHOW\" command to check information about tables, tablespaces, indexes, and more in the database.\n\nSyntax\n```sql\n machbase-neo>> SHOW name;\n```\n\nSHOW INFO\n------\nRetrieve server information.\n```sql\nmachbase-neo>> show info;\n```\n\nSHOW TABLES\n------\nIt displays table information.\n\n-a Using options allows for more detailed information retrieval.\n\n```sql\nmachbase-neo>> show tables;\n\nmachbase-neo>> show tables -a;\n```\n\nSHOW INDEXES \n------\nIt prints the list of indexes.\n```sql\nmachbase-neo>> show indexes;\n```\n\nSHOW INDEXES index name\n------\nIt displays specific index information.\n```sql\nmachbase-neo>> show index idx_name;\n```\n\nSHOW STORAGE\n------\nIt outputs disk usage information.\n```sql\nmachbase-neo>> show storage;\n```\n\nSHOW TABLE-USAGE\n------\nIt prints disk usage information for each table.\n```sql\nmachbase-neo>> show table-usage;\n```\n\nSHOW STATEMENTS\n------\nIt displays the currently executing SQL statement.\n```sql\nmachbase-neo>> show statements;\n```\n\nSHOW USERS\n------\nIt lists the registered user names.\n```sql\nmachbase-neo>> show users;\n```\n\nSHOW TAGINDEXGAP\n------\nIt outputs the gap information used for creating indexes in the TAG table.\n```sql\nmachbase-neo>> show tagindexgap;\n```\n\nSHOW ROLLUPGAP\n------\nIt displays the information about the hourly, minutely, and secondly rollup creation used in the Rollup table.\n```sql\nmachbase-neo>> show rollupgap;\n```\n\nClosing Words\n------\nThe \"show\" command provided by Machbase offers various functionalities ranging from table retrieval to index gap. \nParticularly, options like \"indexgap\" or \"rollupgap\" are helpful in assessing the current progress of index or rollup creation.","result":"","status":true,"height":200,"lang":[["markdown","Markdown"],["SQL","SQL"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":true}]}